Format data for PART

Source: R/PART.R
prep_counts_for_PART.Rd

The function retrieves the counts from the time series object and filters it to only contain relevant genes and samples. The data can also be scaled if the parameter 'scale' is set to TRUE

prep_counts_for_PART(object, target_genes, scale, target_samples)

Arguments

object

A time series object

target_genes

Vector of genes to keep/use

scale

Boolean indicating if the data should be scaled

target_samples

Vector of samples to keep/use

Value

The timeseries object with the added PART count matrix
